<section id="unstub" class="slide">
  <h2>unstub (or unstub!)</h2>

  <p>Removes a stub. On a double, the object will no longer respond to message. On a real object, the original method (if it exists) is restored.</p>

  <script type="syntaxhighlighter" class="brush: ruby">
    describe String do
      it "can restore it's own behavior" do
        expect(String).to receive(:new).and_return("hello")
        expect(String.new("initial string")).to eq("hello")

        expect(String).to receive(:new).and_call_original
        expect(String.new("initial string")).to eq("initial string")
      end
    end
  </script>

</section>
